From: John Vogel <jvogel@stygian.me>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 22:50:21 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] src/loop.c: add missing include

From build log:
--
src/loop.c:22:14: error: expected ';' before 'int'
   22 | EXPORT_SYMBOL int ehd_loop_setup(const char *filename, char **result, bool ro)
      |              ^~~~
      |              ;
src/loop.c:38:14: error: expected ';' before 'int'
   38 | EXPORT_SYMBOL int ehd_loop_release(const char *device)
      |              ^~~~
      |              ;
make[1]: *** [Makefile:865: src/loop.lo] Error 1
--

EXPORT_SYMBOL is defined in src/pam_mount.h.
---
 src/loop.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/loop.c b/src/loop.c
index 1bcdcf3..188ee02 100644
--- a/src/loop.c
+++ b/src/loop.c
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@
 #include <stdbool.h>
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include "libcryptmount.h"
+#include "pam_mount.h"
 #include "config.h"
 
 /**
